    • Method Detail

      • getRollupBasetime

        public static int getRollupBasetime(long timestamp,
                                    RollupInterval interval)
        Calculates the base time for a rollup interval, the time that can be stored in the row key.
        Parameters:
        timestamp - The data point timestamp to calculate from in seconds or milliseconds
        interval - The configured interval object to use for calcaulting the base time with a valid span of 'h', 'd', 'm' or 'y'
        Returns:
        A base time as a unix epoch timestamp in seconds
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the timestamp is negative or the interval has an unsupported span

      • buildRollupQualifier

        public static byte[] buildRollupQualifier(long timestamp,
                                          short flags,
                                          int aggregator_id,
                                          RollupInterval interval)
        Builds a rollup column qualifier, prepending the appender as a string then the offeset on 2 bytes for the interval after a colon with the last four bits reserved for the length and type flags. I.e. <agg>:<offset(flag)> n : 2 bytes
        Parameters:
        timestamp - The data point timestamp
        flags - The length and type (float || int) flags for the value
        aggregator_id - The numeric ID of the aggregator the value maps to.
        interval - The RollupInterval object with data about the interval
        Returns:
        An n byte array to use as the qualifier
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the aggregator is null or empty or the timestamp is too far from the base time to fit within the interval.

      • buildRollupQualifier

        public static byte[] buildRollupQualifier(long timestamp,
                                          int basetime,
                                          short flags,
                                          int aggregator_id,
                                          RollupInterval interval)
        Builds a rollup column qualifier, prepending the appender as a string then the offeset on 2 bytes for the interval after a colon with the last four bits reserved for the length and type flags. I.e. <agg>:<offset(flag)> n : 2 bytes
        Parameters:
        timestamp - The data point timestamp
        basetime - The base timestamp to calculate the offset from
        flags - The length and type (float || int) flags for the value
        aggregator_id - The numeric ID of the aggregator the value maps to.
        interval - The RollupInterval object with data about the interval
        Returns:
        An n byte array to use as the qualifier
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the aggregator is null or empty or the timestamp is too far from the base time to fit within the interval.
